IT doesn’t matter whether you are an executive looking for exclusivity – or just a gym bunny who wants to work out and stay fit. There’s a gym for everyone. Gym membership fees shouldn’t deter you from achieving your goals. Many gyms offer workout spaces with quality training equipment at an affordable price. READ: PIC: CELEBS WHO HIT THE GYM!if(typeof za24_DisplayAd != "undefined") za24_DisplayAd("300x250","2");<a href="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/jump?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" target="_blank"><img src="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/ad?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" border="0" alt=""></a>Planet Fitness and Virgin Active have entry-level packages offering respectable training experiences for as little as R200 per month. At Viva Gym, with branches in Joburg, Pretoria and Port Elizabeth, you pay R250 per month – without a contract. According to Viva, costs are kept low by: “ . . . cutting through all of the unnecessary extras that drive up monthly fees, like swimming pools and steam rooms.” If you want a premium gym, a Virgin Active Collection package with prices from R1 250 to R2 000 a month, is just for you. For that, members enjoy high-performance training facilities, latest cardio and strength equipment, a bank of Wattbikes (as used by Olympic cyclists), and dedicated Pilates and suspension yoga studios. Members also have access to a fully-equipped boardroom with Mac workstations, wireless printing and unlimited Wi-Fi. Members of the Collection health clubs also enjoy a complimentary shoe shine, towel and concierge service. If they need medical attention while at the gym, a suite of wellness experts is on hand, with biokineticists, physiotherapists and dieticians. This service carries an extra cost, as do spa treatments and the “groom den”. ALSO READ: GET BACK IN SHAPE!